  <title>Options</title>
  <section>
    <title>PDF/SVG Page Size</title>
    <p>The <gui>PDF/SVG Page Size</gui> radio buttons select the page size for images saved in those formats.</p>
    <note style="tip">
      <p>The size of the printed page is selectable from the printer dialog at the time of printing and is remembered by the program.</p>
    </note>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>Show / Hide</title>
    <list>
      <item><p>The <gui>Instrument</gui> checkbox will enable or disable the display of the HP logo and instrument identifier on the plot.</p></item>
      <item><p>The <gui>Date &amp; Time</gui> checkbox will enable or disable the display of the time and date on the plot.</p></item>
      <item><p>The <gui>Memory</gui> checkbox will enable or disable the traces saved to the mrmory.</p><p>This option is automatically set when saving a trace to the memory or when loading a JSON file containing a memory trace.</p></item>
    </list>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>Instrument Variant</title>
    <p>The <gui>8970A</gui>, <gui>8970B</gui>, <gui>8970B/20</gui> radio buttons change the behaviour of the program to match the device being controlled.</p>
    <p>The 8970A has a maximum of 81 callibration points and an upper frequency, in mode 1.0, of 1500 MHz</p>
    <p>The 8970B has a maximum of 181 callibration points and an upper frequency, in mode 1.0, of 1600 MHz and, with option 20, 2047 MHz</p>
  </section>



